Gray code and binary representations of long nucleotide sequences   It is known that Gray code (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gray_code), which is widely explored to facilitate error correction in digital communications, uses a special system of relation between binary numbers and decimal numbers.
One can mention about a connection of Gray code with QR codes (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/QR_code).
